modules.description: This module provides functions to construct inline and block-level elements for document structures, handling types like text, emphasis, links, lists, headings, and code blocks. It operates on data types representing inline elements and block elements, with support for attributes and nested content. Concrete use cases include building formatted documents programmatically, generating HTML output, or creating structured content for markdown processing.

This module parses and generates markdown documents using a structured AST representation. It supports operations for constructing and manipulating document elements like headings, lists, tables, and inline formatting with attributes, and provides direct conversions to HTML and S-expressions. Use cases include programmatically generating markdown content, extracting headers for navigation, and converting markdown to HTML with customizable output options.
